Durban - A man was killed and another has been left in critical condition after a car crash on the N3 towards Pietermaritzburg, near the Shongweni off-ramp on Tuesday morning. Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care Paramedics Operations Director said, “Rescue Care and Meditech Paramedics arrived on the scene to find carnage. Two vehicles and a truck had collided before one overturned coming to rest on its roof. One driver had sustained major injuries and unfortunately there was nothing more Paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene. The second driver had sustained moderate injuries and was stabilised on the scene by Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that he required.”  Jamieson also said the traffic was severely affected as most of the national highway was affected by the incident. Police were investigating the circumstances of the crash. Daily News